cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for segmenting epithelial tissue in digitised hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) stained prostatectomy slides using immunohistochemistry (IHC) as reference standard. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for image segmentation, information retrieval (cs.IR) for creating a ground truth dataset, machine learning (cs.LG) for training the U-Net models, deep learning (cs.DL) for the neural network architecture, and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) for the potential application of this system in automated prostate cancer grading.
